  <section class="page-section">
    <p class="eyebrow">World</p>
    <h1>The Rimaeri</h1>
    <p class="lede">The Rimaeri are the people of the Rim. Outsiders may call them Rimmers, but among themselves they are Rimaeri.</p>
    <p>Their identity grows from border life, movement, fairness, and practical ways of living between worlds that do not always match each other neatly.</p>

    <article class="panel">
      <p class="eyebrow">Rim thread</p>
      <h2>Fairness and movement</h2>
      <p>Movement matters in Rimaeri life, but movement alone is not the point. Routes can connect people, goods, memory, duty, and shared knowledge.</p>
      <p>Fairness matters because crossing and exchange affect more than one person. The Rim teaches movement. The Rimaeri show how people live inside it.</p>
      <div class="link-list">
        <a href="/world/the-rim/">Return to the Rim</a>
        <a href="/artefacts/maps/">Reader map</a>
        <a href="/language/lexicon/">Rimaeri in the lexicon</a>
      </div>
    </article>

    <p>Routes, weather, exchange, shared knowledge, and rhythm shape daily life. Fairness and remembrance can carry as much weight as possession or fixed boundaries.</p>
    <p>Rimaeri life is varied. Families, places, duties, and ways of carrying history can differ while still holding a shared sense of belonging to the Rim.</p>
